# Codex-scope secrets — powers the second-opinion reviewer (control/second-opinion.sh).
# Lives as PLAINTEXT secret.codex.env in the workspace (gitignored — never commit it).
#
# If you authenticate the codex CLI with `codex login` (ChatGPT account) instead, you do NOT
# need this scope at all — leave the file absent and secret_exec runs codex bare.
#
# Otherwise set a pay-as-you-go OpenAI API key (prefer a scoped/disposable one):
OPENAI_API_KEY=
